anizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"event":"labeled","commit_id":null,"commit_url":null,"created_at":"2024-09-20T15:02:39Z","label":{"name":"S-Needs-Triage","color":"D876e3"},"performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bevyengine/bevy/issues/comments/2365256927","html_url":"https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/issues/15335#issuecomment-2365256927","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bevyengine/bevy/issues/15335","id":2365256927,"node_id":"IC_kwDODf6-U86M-vTf","user":{"login":"Piefayth","id":4909503,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ5MDk1MDM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4909503?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth","html_url":"https://github.com/Piefayth","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2024-09-21T17:12:23Z","updated_at":"2024-09-21T17:12:23Z","body":"A naive solution would be this, I guess. Seems like when calculating the clip for the child, you need the border size of the parent.\r\n\r\nSurely there's something more clever we could do? \r\n\r\n```rs\r\npub fn extract_uinode_background_colors(\r\n    // ... snip ...\r\n    uinode_query: Extract<\r\n        Query<(\r\n            Entity,\r\n            &Node,\r\n            &GlobalTransform,\r\n            &ViewVisibility,\r\n            Option<&CalculatedClip>,\r\n            Option<&TargetCamera>,\r\n            &BackgroundColor,\r\n            &Style,\r\n            Option<&Parent>,\r\n        )>,\r\n    >,\r\n    node_query: Extract<Query<(&Node, &Style, Option<&Parent>)>>,\r\n) {\r\n    for (\r\n        entity,\r\n        uinode,\r\n        transform,\r\n        view_visibility,\r\n        clip,\r\n        camera,\r\n        background_color,\r\n        style,\r\n        parent,\r\n    ) in &uinode_query\r\n    {\r\n        // ... snip ...\r\n\r\n        // to calculate the parent's border, we need the grandparent's width too...\r\n        let (parent_border, parent_width, grandparent_width) = parent\r\n            .and_then(|parent| node_query.get(parent.get()).ok())\r\n            .map(|(parent_node, parent_style, grandparent)| {\r\n                let parent_width = parent_node.size().x;\r\n                let grandparent_width = grandparent\r\n                    .and_then(|gp| node_query.get(gp.get()).ok())\r\n                    .map(|(gp_node, _, _)| gp_node.size().x)\r\n                    .unwrap_or(ui_logical_viewport_size.x);\r\n        \r\n                (parent_style.border, parent_width, grandparent_width)\r\n            })\r\n            .unwrap_or((UiRect::DEFAULT, ui_logical_viewport_size.x, ui_logical_viewport_size.x));\r\n\r\n        // gross duplicated work\r\n        let parent_left =\r\n            resolve_border_thickness(parent_border.left, grandparent_width, ui_logical_viewport_size);\r\n        let parent_right =\r\n            resolve_border_thickness(parent_border.right, grandparent_width, ui_logical_viewport_size);\r\n        let parent_top =\r\n            resolve_border_thickness(parent_border.top, grandparent_width, ui_logical_viewport_size);\r\n        let parent_bottom =\r\n            resolve_border_thickness(parent_border.bottom, grandparent_width, ui_logical_viewport_size);\r\n\r\n        let left =\r\n            resolve_border_thickness(style.border.left, parent_width, ui_logical_viewport_size);\r\n        let right =\r\n            resolve_border_thickness(style.border.right, parent_width, ui_logical_viewport_size);\r\n        let top =\r\n            resolve_border_thickness(style.border.top, parent_width, ui_logical_viewport_size);\r\n        let bottom =\r\n            resolve_border_thickness(style.border.bottom, parent_width, ui_logical_viewport_size);\r\n\r\n        let border = [left, top, right, bottom];\r\n\r\n        let border_radius = [\r\n            uinode.border_radius.top_left,\r\n            uinode.border_radius.top_right,\r\n            uinode.border_radius.bottom_right,\r\n            uinode.border_radius.bottom_left,\r\n        ];\r\n\r\n        extracted_uinodes.uinodes.insert(\r\n            entity,\r\n            ExtractedUiNode {\r\n                stack_index: uinode.stack_index,\r\n                transform: transform.compute_matrix(),\r\n                color: background_color.0.into(),\r\n                rect: Rect {\r\n                    min: Vec2::ZERO,\r\n                    max: uinode.calculated_size,\r\n                },\r\n                clip: clip.map(|clip| {\r\n                    let mut adj_clip = clip.clip;\r\n                    // actually update the clip position\r\n                    adj_clip.max.x -= parent_left;\r\n                    adj_clip.min.x += parent_right;\r\n\r\n                    adj_clip.max.y -= parent_top;\r\n                    adj_clip.min.y += parent_bottom;\r\n\r\n                    adj_clip\r\n                }),\r\n                image: AssetId::default(),\r\n                atlas_scaling: None,\r\n                flip_x: false,\r\n                flip_y: false,\r\n                camera_entity,\r\n                border,\r\n                border_radius,\r\n                node_type: NodeType::Rect,\r\n            },\r\n        );\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nBefore: Child covers borders\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/52808300-66ed-4507-ac25-8ecefaa3b639)\r\n\r\nAfter: Borders are visible on all sides!\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/41401a50-ac0c-488f-98a2-5c61df6274bf)\r\n","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bevyengine/bevy/issues/comments/2365256927/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"Piefayth","id":4909503,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ5MDk1MDM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4909503?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth","html_url":"https://github.com/Piefayth","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Piefayth/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bevyengine/bevy/issues/comments/2365259796","html_url":"https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/issues/15335#issuecomment-2365259796","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bevyengine/bevy/issues/15335","id":2365259796,"node_id":"IC_kwDODf6-U86M-wAU","user":{"login":"Piefayth","id":4909503,"node_id":"MD